# The database is generated data, not prose. `blindfold-curate` writes LF, so
# checking it out as CRLF on Windows would leave the working tree byte-different from
# what a regeneration produces — harmless for `of_jsonl`, which trims each line, but
# it makes "did regenerating change anything?" impossible to answer by hashing.
*.jsonl text eol=lf

# Shell scripts are run by bash (fetch-vosk.sh, a Trunk build hook). A CRLF checkout on
# Windows leaves stray `\r`s that break the shebang and trailing-token parsing, so keep
# them LF regardless of the platform's autocrlf.
*.sh text eol=lf
